name: linguini with chicken & sauteed vegetables
instructions:
1. Cook linguine according to package instructions (omit salt). Drain and toss with 1 Tbsp of olive oil. 

2. Cut broccoli, carrots, cabbage, and cauliflower into bite-sized pieces. 

3. Mince garlic. 

4. Heat remaining 2 Tbsp oil in a large skillet over medium heat. 

5. Add broccoli, carrots, cabbage, cauliflower and garlic to hot oil.

6. Cook to desired level of tenderness. 

7. Stir in shredded chicken and cooked linguini.

8. Drizzle in soy sauce. 

9. Slice green onions, and cilantro and sprinkle over pasta.
